{"title":"MR and Guinea (Conakry), a short history (from my email)","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/902464949/0/marginalrevolution~MR-and-Guinea-Conakry-a-short-history-from-my-email.html","date":1723007067000,"content":"<p>I will not double indent:</p>\r\n<p>“Dear Tyler,</p>\r\n<p>I am a great fan.  I am currently focused on Guinea (Conakry) and wondered what you might have posted about the country over the years. My search for “Guinea” in Marginal Revolution results in 50 posts:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>In 13 of them you are referring to “guinea pigs”.</li>\r\n<li>In 9 of them you are referring to “Papua New Guinea”.</li>\r\n<li>In 9 you refer to “Equatorial Guinea”.</li>\r\n<li>In 5 of there is no explicit mention of Guinea (I assume the reference to Guinea can be found if one follows the links?)</li>\r\n<li>In 4 you refer to “Guinea Bissau”.</li>\r\n<li>In 4 you refer to “Guinea”, the country of that name with capital in Conakry</li>\r\n<li>In 3 the reference is to the broader region (Gulf of Guinea, etc).</li>\r\n<li>One reference to the island of “New Guinea”.</li>\r\n<li>One reference to the “guinea worm”.</li>\r\n<li>One reference to “guineas” as in the coins.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Of the references to the country of Guinea, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmarginalrevolution.com%2Fmarginalrevolution%2F2007%2F12%2Ffurther-meta-li.html&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7C8db36b86bab94ac7702d08dcb537897f%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C638584497341749222%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=%2BozeM4XZldtE2ZvxGXgDX9GbOIrEO5NrANmbykWB%2BCA%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\">one refers to Bembeya Jazz</a> (good one!), <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmarginalrevolution.com%2Fmarginalrevolution%2F2011%2F05%2Fassorted-links-101.html&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7C8db36b86bab94ac7702d08dcb537897f%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C638584497341758901%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=EQSR%2Fz6IhvS080cNzYryE7rI4GodZ0EVRlva4hI8lXA%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\">another to press coverage</a> from that country on the DSK affair in 2011, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmarginalrevolution.com%2Fmarginalrevolution%2F2009%2F08%2Fchinaafrica-fact-of-the-day.html&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7C8db36b86bab94ac7702d08dcb537897f%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C638584497341765762%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=2PXOuYudbTbhfa2vIVZF899gkNEtwfogq4r6echGIss%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\">one mentions Guinea</a> as one of the countries of origin for Africans in Guangzhou, and a final one appropriately mentions it on the topic of <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fmarginalrevolution.com%2Fmarginalrevolution%2F2009%2F12%2Fwikipedia-knowledge-deserts-africa-fact-of-the-day.html&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7C8db36b86bab94ac7702d08dcb537897f%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C638584497341771713%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=c6biwXUCrvW07SjSE5wAem7FnWOSeycGyRsVwJsjzx4%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\">“Wikipedia knowledge deserts”</a>.</p>\r\n<p>None of these is a dedicated post to the country, something each of the other Guineas does enjoy on Marginal Revolution. I wondered if you might consider redressing the balance?</p>\r\n<p>If it helps, here I write for the Centre for African Studies at Singapore’s Nanyang Technological University on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://nam11.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ntu.edu.sg%2Fcas%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fdetails%2Fhow-asia-is-driving-the-mining-boom-in-guinea&amp;data=05%7C02%7Ctcowen%40gmu.edu%7C8db36b86bab94ac7702d08dcb537897f%7C9e857255df574c47a0c00546460380cb%7C0%7C0%7C638584497341777506%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp;sdata=4hwYBoJdnNTId6e0a8ZAJ7ZgUTrvRUR53Zzo9Bt79uI%3D&amp;reserved=0\" target=\"_blank\">how Asian demand, investment and policies is driving a mining boom in Guinea</a>. Guinea is posed to be one of the top 2 growing economies in the world over the next five years on the back of the $20 billion Simandou iron ore mining project. You heard it here first!</p>\r\n<p>Cordialement,</p>\r\n<p>Bernabé Sánchez”</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/08/mr-and-guinea-conakry-a-short-history-from-my-email.html\">MR and Guinea (Conakry), a short history (from my email)</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/902464949/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/902464949/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/902464949/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/902464949/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/x.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/19/902464949/margina